title: You Are My Candy Girl
body:
read it on the AO3 at https://ift.tt/2q6pAGU

by ThisIsACreativeName42

Pepper eloped with Happy. He had been expecting this really, their longing glances and flirting weren’t really subtle. The way he found out wasn’t subtle either, a few months of that light flirting building up to them telling him, and him taking it in stride and moving on as best he can. The problem now, months later, is that someone caught his eye. Someone he was supposed to hate. He couldn’t help it really, the man who moved into the tower was charming and attractive, long brown hair swept back into a messy bun, making him wonder how that scruffy stubble would feel against his face. He couldn’t ask out the man who killed his Mom- but it wasn’t him was it? It was HYDRA.

tags: let pepper keep the fire juice 2018
summary: Marvel should have let Pepper keep those powers she got from the fire juice stuff in Iron Man 3, because it’s established that...
body: Marvel should have let Pepper keep those powers she got from the fire juice stuff in Iron Man 3, because it’s established that the people that can’t tolerate the juice burn up almost immediately once it’s administered.  Pepper could clearly tolerate it since she wasn’t ya know, dead.  Pepper should have been allowed to keep her powers, she would have become a further invaluable asset to the Avengers.  And from a writing standpoint what was the point of giving Pepper powers if they were gonna write them away five minutes later?
